<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Panda Bao Buns | Taste The Movies</title>
</head>
<body>

  <header>
    <h1>Taste The Movies</h1>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section>
      <div>
        <img src="images/placeholder.png" alt="Panda Bao Buns from Turning Red" />
      </div>
      <div>
        <h2>Steamed Pork or Veggie Buns</h2>
        <p><strong>Description:</strong></p>
        <p>Inspired by Mei's mom's cooking and Pixar’s short *Bao*. Soft, steamed buns filled with either pork or mushrooms for a savory treat.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div>
        <h3>Ingredients</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>For dough:</strong> 2 cups flour</li>
          <li>1 tbsp sugar</li>
          <li>1 tsp yeast</li>
          <li>¾ cup warm water</li>
          <li><strong>For filling:</strong> ground pork or mushrooms</li>
          <li>1 garlic clove, minced</li>
          <li>2 tbsp soy sauce</li>
          <li>1 tsp sesame oil</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3>Instructions</h3>
        <ol>
          <li>Mix dough ingredients and let the dough rise for 1 hour.</li>
          <li>Prepare filling by cooking pork or mushrooms with garlic, soy sauce, and sesame oil.</li>
          <li>Roll dough into small balls, flatten each ball, add filling, and pinch to close.</li>
          <li>Steam the buns in a bamboo steamer for 15–20 minutes until fluffy.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer>
  </footer>

</body>
</html>

